headline: Dell leads S&P 500 gains, Nvidia CEO confirms xAI investment
summary: Yahoo Finance's John Hyland tracks Wednesday's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Dell (DELL) stock's price target was upgraded by multiple firms, including JPMorgan (JPM), Citi (C), and UBS (UBS). Gold (GC=F) continues to rally, trading above the $4,000 mark. Nvidia (NVDA) CEO Jensen Huang confirmed in a CNBC interview on Wednesday that the company will be investing in Tesla (TSLA) CEO Elon Musk's artificial intelligence company, xAI (XAAI.PVT). Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Dell’s Valuation in Focus as OpenAI Plans Major AI Server Investment
summary: If you’re standing at the crossroads wondering whether Dell Technologies’ stock deserves a place in your portfolio, you’re definitely not alone. The company has been on many investors’ radar, especially after a series of price surges that have made both short-term traders and long-term holders take notice. Just in the past week, Dell’s shares climbed 6.4%, capping off a hefty 20.9% gain over the last month. If you zoom out further, the numbers are just as impressive, with shares up 29.5%...
